item.title: Loool, bots mainly
item.dc:creator: @drubrkletern drubrkletern
item.description:
@drubrkletern wrote:

[quote=“LKCTheReturn, post:17, topic:419570”][quote author=Frell link=topic=522114.msg3796113#msg3796113 date=1319643850]
It’s funny because fags on rs buddy forums claim that rs is too repetitive and jagex forces you to do menial tasks that take forever to level you.

And they probably miss old 2007 rs also.

Remember?

When there were no smart bots
When skilling took way longer…
Less fun mini games for skill xp…

About 1/2 of the player base was lost, and idiots on rs buddy forums are saying “Lololol fagex needs r money they’ll undo the nuke watch lolol fail.”

Runescape with bots: 187k online
Runescape with no bots in 2007: 260k
Runescape with no bots NOW: 100k

Wont last long at all, the game will feel so much more lively and less like robo world with advertising everywhere.

Runescape now with bots gone, new players, and veteran members returning: probably around 300k easily by mid 2012.
[/quote]

I have a feeling that by mid 2012 there wouldn’t be an increase of 200-240k players. Maybe an increase of around 20-100k but most likely not 200k+. You also have to take into mind that once their new game is released, and if that game is successful, a ton of players would most likely convert over to the new game.

That is only my opinion though.[/quote]
If this does happen… then we shall have a upper edge on more than 100k players, and I can be considered a higher class :feelsrich:
